<h1>@HI{{ni}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> <strong>@HI{{ni}}</strong>
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{ni}}</strong> is a particle which:
<ul>
<li> indicates where something is "in", "at" or "on"
<li> indicates the location of an action "in" or "at"
<li> indicates time
<li> indicates movement from a larger place to a smaller place
<li> indicates movement towards a place
<li> indicates the object of an action
<li> indicates the recipient of an action
<li> indicates the result of a change or impending change
<li> indicates a condition that already exists
<li> marks the agent of a passive verb
<li> indicates the person made to do something in a causative sentence
<li> indicates the agent of a causative-passive verb
<li> joins nouns (usually three or more)
<li> indicates a pair of people ofthings that are often mentioned together
<li> indicates the basis on whichan action takes place
</ul>
</p>

